[[Image:Abutments (PSF).png|several abutments|thumb]]

===Etymology===
First attested in 1644; engineering sense first attested in 1793. From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|aboutement|lang=fro}}.<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=11}}</ref> Equivalent to {{suffix|abut|ment}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əˈbʌt.mn̩t/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/əˈbʌt.mn̩t/}}
* {{rhymes|ʌtmənt}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The point of [[junction]] between two things, in particular a support, that abuts. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|engineering|architecture|lang=en}} The solid portion of a structure that supports the lateral pressure of an [[arch]] or [[vault]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|engineering|lang=en}} A [[construction]] that supports the ends of a [[bridge]]; a structure that anchors the cables on a [[suspension bridge]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# Something that [[abut]]s, or on which something abuts. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# The state of [[abutting]].
# {{context|architecture|lang=en}} That [[element]] that shares a common boundary or surface with its neighbor.
# {{context|dentistry|lang=en}} The tooth that supports a [[denture]] or [[bridge]].
# A fixed point or surface where resistance is obtained.
#: The [[fulcrum]] acted as an '''abutment'''.

